44 Tri-Spec Cleric</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 424<br> <font color=#000000>(6/10/03 10:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some undocumented things in 1.62</span><hr size=1> I thought somebody already said we got a &quot;smite&quot; effect for Flurry.<br>
<br>
Damn, that sucks, a fire proc.<br>
<br>
They should get an effect for BladeDance (besides making the RA much, much better) and use this for flurry, only a targeted one, not AOE.<br>
<br>
It should be sort of like the Midgard sword/hammer buff and sort of like the Paladin damage chant, only a bit more aggressive and sudden.<br>
<br>
Sort of like Haste only with weapons visible, within the storm. <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Would you think a man going naked with a sword is scarier than a man going naked with an axe? </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - Tatsumaru<br>
<br>
<br>
Blame MyBlades, (Golden Hands of Gain)<br>
Toast-munching backflipping art critic of Excalibur</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#000000>(6/10/03 2:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some undocumented things in 1.62</span><hr size=1> It procs often, sticks with a reasonable reliablity from what i see, and does have a noticable effect from my experience. Rarely do i ever see it get resisted two times in a row. I think what many people are seeing is that once the DT effect is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>on</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> someone, they resist it untill it runs out. It can't be reapplied over-and-over to keep someone in DT non-stop. Once they have the 'dirt cloud' around their head, it's on them, and they will resist.<br>
<br>
Dirty Tricks does <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pop you out of combat, period. I've tested it many times in duels, and it makes a huge difference to the odds of me winning against classes that are usually total duel dominators. Paladins and Friars now have to work hard for a win against me. I tried several duels without, and got totally smeared. As soon as i pulled it out and used it, the tables turned in a big way, with me winning, or the fight being <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>very</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> close.<br>
<br>
I admit it's still a chance to proc, a chance to stick, and a chance to make them fumble. I'm not too fond of a chance, of a chance, of a chance, either. But it's not as bad as many people seem to be making it out to be. Two Merc's working together can really shut down a bunch of tanks with it now, and a single Merc' can save an entire group who get in trouble in PvE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#000000>(6/10/03 2:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some undocumented things in 1.62</span><hr size=1> Edit: Thank you EzBoards for puting my post in the wrong post thread. &lt;Sigh&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tatsumaruiii>TatsumaruIII</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#000000>(6/10/03 5:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some undocumented things in 1.62</span><hr size=1> I'v used flurry a few times on pendragon, and was a cleric smite spell (little ball over the head). I liked how it looked.<br>
<br>
Although I use it a lot in RvR, I don't ever get to see the effect. Too much junk in my way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . A fire effect would explain why I can't see it - plenty of fire wizards out there, and a high chance one is blasting on my target. I try to solo ones out and flurry just to see, but no luck. Maybe i'll duel someone, should be easier then.<br>
<br>
DT is resisted, just flat out. I posted about it on the VN boards, and k8t believes our problem is related to the resists bug that's currently out (people in high-scaled PvE raids were experinceing TONS of resists from mobs than normal. Most likly effecting RvR, too, but I havn't heard much of any offical word on this yet).<br>
<br>
Also, I gotta give mythic some credit. Flank, once/if it lands, does real good damage. My anytime amy slash does about 30+ where flank now does 60+ (from 40-50ish). Shadow's Rain also does the damage, and is easier to pull off with it's med to-hit bonus. Still, though, Flank <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>NEEDS</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a to hit bonus of some sort. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
Voas - 24 Scout</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fester@lighttanksofdaoc>Fester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#000000>(6/11/03 5:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some undocumented things in 1.62</span><hr size=1> Regarding the Popping out of duel on dirt<br>
<br>
The old dirt worked fine in duels. Now when I try to use it it says &quot;You drink a potion&quot; &quot;Duel has been cancelled&quot; or something like that.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#000000>(6/11/03 1:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some undocumented things in 1.62</span><hr size=1> I have never seen this, in a duel, or in RvR when i use DT. And i use it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>alot</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> now. in fact, i was in Dark Falls last night farming coin, and killed off two assassins (One Nightshade and one Shadowblade) who made the poor choise of trying to stop my farming fun. Both times i used DT while in 1-on-1 combat, and i totally shut them down. In fact it was so helpful killing the 2nd Shadowblade, i only needed DT and Flurry to kick their butt. (Partly because i had already used my IP and Purge on the first Nightshade, who was tougher)<br>
<br>
If you're getting this problem, it's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>totally</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a bug. Try removing the DT icon from your Q-bar and replacing it. If this doesn't help, make a bug appeal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=253.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=253.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=253.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.threadControl?topicID=253.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=253.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=253.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr ali